title: Grateful Dead Live at Campus Stadium, UCSB on 1974-05-25
description:
Set One  	U.S. Blues ; Mexicali Blues ; Deal ; Jack Straw ; Scarlet Begonias ; Beat It On Down The Line ; Brown Eyed Women ; Me And My Uncle ; Sugaree ; El Paso ; China Cat Sunflower > I Know You Rider ; Around And Around 

Set Two 	The Promised Land ; Ship Of Fools ; Big River ; Tennessee Jed ; Truckin' > Jam > Space > Let It Grow > Wharf Rat ; Sugar Magnolia > Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad > One More Saturday Night 

Encore	 	Casey Jones

reviews.review_text:
Overall Excellent A few dents in the fender, scratches on the paint,

but otherwise,

Runs great!

Billy K! Please check in with the funky drummer, Billy K, on GDTRFB. He is simply on fire. He sounds like he is playing with 4 arms and 4 legs. Tremendous stuff!

Oh, and a great show to boot.
Fast and Furious China Cat Sunflower! What a great one! Maybe just a great song. Screaming guitars, the build ups and drops to the beat. Definitely worth hearing this one.

Yes Serial Killa, you are correct. This China Cat Sunflower is a good one. Maybe just a great song? Yes, maybe it is. Billy K is laying it down the funkiest I've ever heard and everybody is just getting down hard. Pretty damn near perfect except Phil drops out in the key change after the second verse. They nail the jam right before segue into IKYR though. Sound quality is top notch to my ears. I think this may be my new favorite China Cat. Looking forward to listening to the rest.
Morning comes... Truckin > Let it Grow
